    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - SERVICE CAB - SERVICE CAB - DRIVER CONTROL MODULE (DCM) INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>DRIVER CONTROL MODULE (DCM) INSTALLATION</title>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">TO AVOID CLEARANCE PROBLEMS INSTALL THE DCM BEFORE THE IP. IF THE INSTRUMENT PANEL IS
                ALREADY INSTALLED, LOOSEN THE RETAINER SCREWS AND LIFT THE IP PARTIALLY OUT OF THE WAY TO INSTALL THE
                DCM.
            </emph>
        </para>
        <para>To Install the DCM see
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602702">Figure 2</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602703">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
        </para>
